div.p:
Mr. Welles: The Committee for a Jewish Army has been besieging the White House. McIntyreMarvin H. McIntyre, Secretary to President Roosevelt. eventually sent them to me. They were then thinking of a huge delegation to convince the British that
the Jewish Army ought to go forward. They have finally got their suggestions to a point where they wish to send four people, namely:
Alfred A. Strelsin of New York;
Kenneth Leslie of the “Protestant Digest”;
Andrew L. Somers, a Member of Congress, and
Peter H. Bergson, a Palestinian expert,
